  <h1>App Shells</h1>
  <p class="lead">Application shell layouts for web apps, dashboards, and admin interfaces. These patterns provide the structural foundation for your application's UI.</p>

  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>App shells define the overall structure of your application, organizing navigation, content areas, and auxiliary panels. Choose a layout based on your application's navigation needs and content complexity.</p>
      <p><strong>Key features:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Semantic HTML5 structure with header, nav, main, and aside</li>
        <li>Responsive layouts that adapt to different screen sizes</li>
        <li>Flexible content areas using layout primitives</li>
        <li>Accessible navigation patterns with proper ARIA labels</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Stacked Layout</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>The traditional layout with a header on top and main content below. Best for content-focused applications where vertical space is important.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/shell-stacked.html"
      url="https://app.example.com/dashboard"
      title="Stacked Layout"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="shell-stacked.html">&lt;body&gt;
  &lt;header&gt;
    &lt;a href="/" class="logo"&gt;AppName&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;nav class="horizontal pills" aria-label="Main navigation"&gt;
      &lt;ul&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/dashboard" aria-current="page"&gt;Dashboard&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/projects"&gt;Projects&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/reports"&gt;Reports&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/settings"&gt;Settings&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/nav&gt;
    &lt;layout-cluster data-gap="s"&gt;
      &lt;button class="button small icon-only"&gt;
        &lt;icon-wc name="bell"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
      &lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;button class="button small icon-only"&gt;
        &lt;icon-wc name="user"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
      &lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/layout-cluster&gt;
  &lt;/header&gt;

  &lt;main&gt;
    &lt;layout-stack data-gap="l"&gt;
      &lt;h1&gt;Dashboard&lt;/h1&gt;
      &lt;!-- Page content here --&gt;
    &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
  &lt;/main&gt;

  &lt;footer&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&amp;copy; 2026 AppName&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/footer&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Sidebar + Content</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>A fixed sidebar navigation with a main content area. Ideal for dashboards and admin interfaces with many navigation items.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/shell-sidebar.html"
      url="https://app.example.com/dashboard"
      title="Sidebar Layout"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="shell-sidebar.html">&lt;body&gt;
  &lt;layout-sidebar data-sidebar-width="narrow" data-gap="none"&gt;
    &lt;aside&gt;
      &lt;layout-stack data-gap="l"&gt;
        &lt;a href="/" class="logo"&gt;AppName&lt;/a&gt;
        &lt;nav class="vertical" aria-label="Main navigation"&gt;
          &lt;ul&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/dashboard" aria-current="page"&gt;
              &lt;icon-wc name="home"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt; Dashboard
            &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/projects"&gt;
              &lt;icon-wc name="folder"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt; Projects
            &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/reports"&gt;
              &lt;icon-wc name="chart-bar"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt; Reports
            &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/settings"&gt;
              &lt;icon-wc name="cog"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt; Settings
            &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
          &lt;/ul&gt;
        &lt;/nav&gt;
      &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
    &lt;/aside&gt;

    &lt;div class="content-wrapper"&gt;
      &lt;header&gt;
        &lt;h1&gt;Dashboard&lt;/h1&gt;
        &lt;layout-cluster data-gap="s"&gt;
          &lt;input type="search" placeholder="Search..." /&gt;
          &lt;button class="button icon-only"&gt;
            &lt;icon-wc name="user"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
          &lt;/button&gt;
        &lt;/layout-cluster&gt;
      &lt;/header&gt;

      &lt;main&gt;
        &lt;!-- Page content here --&gt;
      &lt;/main&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/layout-sidebar&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Multi-Column Layout</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>A three-column layout with sidebar navigation, main content, and a right panel. Perfect for email clients, chat applications, or content management systems.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/shell-multi-column.html"
      url="https://mail.example.com/inbox"
      title="Multi-Column Layout"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="shell-multi-column.html">&lt;body&gt;
  &lt;div class="app-shell"&gt;
    &lt;aside class="sidebar-nav"&gt;
      &lt;layout-stack data-gap="m"&gt;
        &lt;a href="/" class="logo"&gt;Mail&lt;/a&gt;
        &lt;button class="button primary"&gt;Compose&lt;/button&gt;
        &lt;nav class="vertical" aria-label="Mail folders"&gt;
          &lt;ul&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/inbox" aria-current="page"&gt;Inbox &lt;span class="badge"&gt;12&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/sent"&gt;Sent&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/drafts"&gt;Drafts&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/archive"&gt;Archive&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
          &lt;/ul&gt;
        &lt;/nav&gt;
      &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
    &lt;/aside&gt;

    &lt;main class="message-list"&gt;
      &lt;header&gt;
        &lt;h1&gt;Inbox&lt;/h1&gt;
        &lt;input type="search" placeholder="Search mail..." /&gt;
      &lt;/header&gt;
      &lt;ul class="messages"&gt;
        &lt;!-- Message list items --&gt;
      &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/main&gt;

    &lt;aside class="message-detail"&gt;
      &lt;!-- Selected message content --&gt;
    &lt;/aside&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Collapsible Sidebar</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>A sidebar that can collapse to icons only, using native <code>&lt;details&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;summary&gt;</code> elements. Great for maximizing content space while keeping navigation accessible.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/shell-collapsible.html"
      url="https://app.example.com/dashboard"
      title="Collapsible Sidebar"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="shell-collapsible.html">&lt;body&gt;
  &lt;div class="app-shell"&gt;
    &lt;details class="sidebar" open&gt;
      &lt;summary&gt;
        &lt;icon-wc name="menu"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
        &lt;span class="sr-only"&gt;Toggle sidebar&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;/summary&gt;
      &lt;layout-stack data-gap="l" class="sidebar-content"&gt;
        &lt;a href="/" class="logo"&gt;AppName&lt;/a&gt;
        &lt;nav class="vertical" aria-label="Main navigation"&gt;
          &lt;ul&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/dashboard" aria-current="page"&gt;
              &lt;icon-wc name="home"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
              &lt;span class="nav-label"&gt;Dashboard&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/projects"&gt;
              &lt;icon-wc name="folder"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
              &lt;span class="nav-label"&gt;Projects&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="/reports"&gt;
              &lt;icon-wc name="chart-bar"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
              &lt;span class="nav-label"&gt;Reports&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
          &lt;/ul&gt;
        &lt;/nav&gt;
      &lt;/layout-stack&gt;
    &lt;/details&gt;

    &lt;main&gt;
      &lt;!-- Page content here --&gt;
    &lt;/main&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Configuration</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>App shells use these layout elements and attributes:</p>
    </layout-text>

    <h3>Layout Sidebar</h3>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Values</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-sidebar-width</code></td>
          <td><code>narrow</code> <code>wide</code></td>
          <td>Sets the sidebar width. Default is approximately 20rem.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-gap</code></td>
          <td><code>none</code> <code>s</code> <code>m</code> <code>l</code> <code>xl</code></td>
          <td>Gap between sidebar and content.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-content-min</code></td>
          <td>Number (percentage)</td>
          <td>Minimum content width before stacking. Default is 50.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Layout Stack</h3>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Values</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-gap</code></td>
          <td><code>xs</code> <code>s</code> <code>m</code> <code>l</code> <code>xl</code></td>
          <td>Vertical spacing between stack items.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Layout Cluster</h3>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Values</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-gap</code></td>
          <td><code>xs</code> <code>s</code> <code>m</code> <code>l</code> <code>xl</code></td>
          <td>Horizontal spacing between items.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-justify</code></td>
          <td><code>start</code> <code>center</code> <code>end</code> <code>space-between</code></td>
          <td>Horizontal alignment of items.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Usage Notes</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Full height:</strong> Use <code>min-block-size: 100vh</code> or <code>min-block-size: 100dvh</code> on the body or wrapper to fill the viewport</li>
        <li><strong>Sticky elements:</strong> Use <code>position: sticky</code> for headers and sidebars that should stay visible while scrolling</li>
        <li><strong>Responsive:</strong> <code>layout-sidebar</code> automatically stacks on narrow viewports based on <code>data-content-min</code></li>
        <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Include skip links, proper heading hierarchy, and ARIA labels on navigation landmarks</li>
        <li><strong>Content overflow:</strong> Set <code>overflow: auto</code> on scrollable regions, keeping sidebars fixed</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
  </section>

